:71:"https://i.pinimg.com/736x/f6/c6/9a/f6c69afce0d58e1ea1e2ce3c6bfb452f.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRYIwRat15J1jKzqywiZ5UTmn97liO5ai1J6w";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:319;s:6:"height";i:736;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/614248836658798948/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:56:{i:0;s:155:"The chair conformation is a six-membered ring in which atoms 2 3 5 and 6 lie in the same plane atom 1 lies above the plane and atom 4 lies below the plane.";i:1;s:94:"With this conformation the bond angles are 1109 degrees much closer to the ideal 1095 degrees.";i:2;s:117:"The chair conformation has alternating axial up axial down so once you have that single axial substituent move on to.";i:3;s:82:"Alternate your axial substituents up and down all the way around your cyclohexane.";i:4;s:45:"Every carbon on the chair conformation has 1.";i:5;s:112:"Looking at the glucopyranose from above you now can easily draw the chair conformation for it in a general form.";i:6;s:180:"Haworth projection and chair conformation of glucopyranose And just as easily you can show a chair conformations specifically for the α-D-glucopyranose and the β-D-glucopyranose.";i:7;s:124:"The tert-butyl group needs to be placed in the equatorial bond as it is the lowest energy or highest stability conformation.";i:8;s:123:"If the tert-butyl group is placed in the axial bond then the chair has the highest energy or the least stable conformation.";i:9;s:74:"Always place the largesthighest priority group in the equatorial position.";i:10;s:70:"However keep in mind that the geometry of the cyclohexane needs to be.";i:11;s:64:"Number the ring and draw any chair conformation of the compound.";i:12;s:73:"Draw the second chair conformation ring-flip-check this post if not sure.";i:13;s:24:"And now the stabilities.";i:14;s:76:"For each chair conformer add the energy of all the groups on axial position.";i:15;s:94:"In the first conformer we have two chlorines in axial positions so the total steric strain is.";i:16;s:81:"My approach is to assume that the dioxane is going to be in a chair conformation.";i:17;s:110:"Im much better at converting six membered rings to the chair if I start with the ring completely in the plane.";i:18;s:182:"In this case that means redrawing the original so that the oxygens are in the plane and the isobutyl and methyl groups are viewed as substituents off the dioxane left side of figure.";i:19;s:117:"Like the chair conformation all of the C C C bond angles of the boat conformation are 1095 so it has no angle strain.";i:20;s:43:"However it does have other types of strain.";i:21;s:109:"The two red hydrogens called flagpole hydrogens approach each other too closely and cause some steric strain.";i:22;s:65:"In addition the conformations about the green bonds are eclipsed.";i:23;s:272:"Chair structures are considered to be conformationally mobile meaning they are flexible not as much so as a straight chain alkane but more so than any of the other smaller rings and because of this flexibility they flip from one possible chair to the other possible chair.";i:24;s:95:"The different conformations are called conformers a blend of the words conformation and isomer.";i:25;s:52:"The chair conformation is the most stable conformer.";i:26;s:80:"At 25 C 9999 of all molecules in a cyclohexane solution adopt this conformation.";i:27;s:111:"To begin start by drawing two lines that are parallel to each other but not perfectly horizontal as shown here.";i:28;s:76:"Next add a downward-pointing V tip to one end this is the tail of the chair.";i:29;s:84:"Finally add an upward-pointing V tip to the other end this is the nose of the chair.";i:30;s:68:"The steps involved in drawing the chair conformation of cyclohexane.";i:31;s:58:"This video is about Stereoisomerism of Chair Conformation.";i:32;s:94:"In this video I explain how to draw the cis and trans stereoisomers of 12-dimethylcyclohexane.";i:33;s:155:"The chair conformation is a six-membered ring in which atoms 2 3 5 and 6 lie in the same plane atom 1 lies above the plane and atom 4 lies below the plane.";i:34;s:94:"With this conformation the bond angles are 1109 degrees much closer to the ideal 1095 degrees.";i:35;s:139:"The key difference between chair and boat conformation is that chair conformation has low energy whereas boat conformation has high energy.";i:36;s:240:"The terms chair conformation and boat conformation come under organic chemistry and they are mainly applicable to cyclohexaneThese are two different structures in which the cyclohexane molecule can exist but they have different stabilities.";i:37;s:146:"Chair conformation is the term used in organic chemistry that represents the chair-like structure of a carbon ring consisting of six carbon atoms.";i:38;s:46:"There may be the presence of substituents for.";i:39;s:108:"At room temperature theres enough energy for the molecule to contort and achieve another chair conformation.";i:40;s:108:"On the right you may notice that the red-colored hydrogen atoms are now in a different chemical environment.";i:41;s:56:"These hydrogen atoms are in the equatorial conformation.";i:42;s:117:"The ground state conformation of cyclohexane is a fully staggered conformation which is shaped somewhat like a chair.";i:43;s:105:"In this conformation there is no torsional strain at all and as we shall see later no strain of any kind.";i:44;s:68:"Cyclohexane is unique in being the only cyclic hydrocarbon which is.";i:45;s:155:"The chair conformation is a six-membered ring in which atoms 2 3 5 and 6 lie in the same plane atom 1 lies above the plane and atom 4 lies below the plane.";i:46;s:94:"With this conformation the bond angles are 1109 degrees much closer to the ideal 1095 degrees.";i:47;s:88:"All the carbon-hydrogen bonds are also fully staggered eliminating the torsional strain.";i:48;s:117:"- The high-energy intermediate conformation of cyclohexane as it converts from one chair conformation into the other.";i:49;s:39:"- footrest flips upward forms the boat.";i:50;s:82:"- highest energy point is where the footrest is planar wthe sides of the molecule.";i:51;s:23:"Axial Equatorial posns.";i:52;s:130:"A discrete hexanuclear zirconium metallocycle has been synthesized isolated and characterized by single-crystal X-ray diffraction.";i:53;s:63:"It is sustained in a chair-like conformation by glycolic acids.";i:54;s:120:"Formation and growth of the complex has been observed using in situ time-resolved dynamic light scattering measurements.";i:55;s:32:"You have access to this article.";}}